Diagram 3 (Calm)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par In response to black \'a1\'e3, it is useless for white to attempt to create more eyespace with 1. Black 2 (or 3) is calm. If white plays at 3, black plays at 4 and that's it.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Instead of 3, if white plays at \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , black a throw-in at \b\f1 B\b0\f0  and it becomes the same as the previous diagram.
\par }
